# Personal Productivity System — Phase 1A Walkthrough

This document outlines the foundation architectural components implemented during Phase 1A of the Personal Productivity System development.

> [!NOTE]
> Phase 1A establishes the foundation. All database tables, repositories, Hilt dependency injection bindings, navigation graphs, and core styling assets have been configured, enabling a compiling base project.

---

## Architectural Overview

The application follows clean architecture principles with a decoupled layer design.

```mermaid
graph TD
    UI[Compose Navigation / Views] --> VM[ViewModels - Phase 1B/C/D]
    VM --> Repos[Repository Layer: combines DAOs]
    Repos --> DAOs[Room DAOs]
    DAOs --> DB[Room AppDatabase]
    DI[Hilt AppModule] -.-> Repos
    DI -.-> DB
```

1. **Presentation Layer (`ui`)**: UI scaffolding, typography, colors, navigation graph, and entry screens.
2. **Data Layer (`data`)**: Database models, DAOs, repositories, and Hilt setup to manage SQLite transactions.
3. **Service Layer (`service`)**: Handles system-level triggers (e.g. boot receiver) to restore application scheduling configurations.

