### 2. Database Entities (`data/model`)

All 7 core SQLite entities are fully defined:

- **[Reminder.kt](file:///c:/Users/Kshitij%20Sharma/Desktop/Omnis/Magnum%20Opus/Personal%20Manager/app/src/main/java/com/productivity/app/data/model/Reminder.kt)**: Manages alarms with details like reminder types (medicine, travel, meeting, etc.), priorities (low, medium, high), recurrence rule strings, and snooze durations.
- **[ScheduleEvent.kt](file:///c:/Users/Kshitij%20Sharma/Desktop/Omnis/Magnum%20Opus/Personal%20Manager/app/src/main/java/com/productivity/app/data/model/ScheduleEvent.kt)**: Represents events, appointments, deadlines, and meetings including start/end timestamps and locations.
- **[ProgressTracker.kt](file:///c:/Users/Kshitij%20Sharma/Desktop/Omnis/Magnum%20Opus/Personal%20Manager/app/src/main/java/com/productivity/app/data/model/ProgressTracker.kt)**: Maps active courses and projects including total units, completed units count, and labels for active milestones.
- **[ProgressUnit.kt](file:///c:/Users/Kshitij%20Sharma/Desktop/Omnis/Magnum%20Opus/Personal%20Manager/app/src/main/java/com/productivity/app/data/model/ProgressUnit.kt)**: Individual units of work (e.g. course modules or project milestones) linked to `ProgressTracker` via Foreign Key cascade delete constraints.
- **[Checklist.kt](file:///c:/Users/Kshitij%20Sharma/Desktop/Omnis/Magnum%20Opus/Personal%20Manager/app/src/main/java/com/productivity/app/data/model/Checklist.kt)**: Manages checklists and marks template states for reusable templates.
- **[ChecklistItem.kt](file:///c:/Users/Kshitij%20Sharma/Desktop/Omnis/Magnum%20Opus/Personal%20Manager/app/src/main/java/com/productivity/app/data/model/ChecklistItem.kt)**: Specific tasks inside a checklist with completion states and sorting orders.
- **[NoteLog.kt](file:///c:/Users/Kshitij%20Sharma/Desktop/Omnis/Magnum%20Opus/Personal%20Manager/app/src/main/java/com/productivity/app/data/model/NoteLog.kt)**: Stores note metadata (type, date, tags) and holds deep-linking URLs to launch individual pages inside the Notion application.

